blog.name: the-isolated-jellyfish
blog.title: Hallucinogenic Waters
blog.description: The inside of me is dark, and fizzes, with a million sepia stars. Your insides are burning like the sun, and know laughter, deep and violent. Each time we come close the wolrd blurrs. I can't see you. I spin. I lose everything. I touch something hiding beyond the flat grass of this world. A yellow claw with glass mosaic fingernails. It closes my eyes.

title: The Thing That’s Coming
body:
That one thing that bothers me.

I’m not even sure, to this day, what it is.

Like the voice of a tiny mouse chorus in my head,

it plays with my knowledge of the universe

and its physical manifestation around me,

distorting it

until it feels unreal.

Is that why I have anxiety? 

Because something more real than I am is rubbing up against

what’s inside me?

Is it like the movement of tectonic plates?

But then, how’s that a good thing?

I don’t know how other people, blank and anonymous

even manage to look at the look in my eyes.

I don’t know how vast cities of wasted potential

just continue on.

But I do know that, when we hear that boom

and something falls from the sky, 

I’ll be ready. 

As masses of people wave their hands and freak out, 

I won’t buy this mass hysteria

because the thing that’s coming

is a calm thing 

and knows me too well.
